window.bookSummaryJSON = "Tautly narrated and excruciatingly suspenseful, <i>Double Indemnity</i> gives us an X-ray view of guilt, of duplicity, and of the kind of obsessive, loveless love that devastates everything it touches. First published in 1936, this novel reaffirmed James M. Cain as a virtuoso of the <i>roman noir</i>."; 
